{
  "texts": [
    "of ZTF reach g ∼ 20.8, r ∼ 20.6, and i ∼ 20.0 mag (AB system) for a 30 s exposure (Masci et al. 2019).",
    "Using light curves from ZTF Data Release 7 (DR7), Guo et al. (2022) measured continuum lags for a large sample of type 1 AGNs at z < 0.8, among which 38 objects (the \"core\"sample) have high-quality interband lag measurements from both JAVELIN and ICCF.",
    "We apply EzTaoX to the g-and r-band ZTF light curves of the core-sample AGNs from Guo et al. (2022), and find that the lags measured with EzTaoX are broadly consistent with those obtained using JAVELIN and ICCF.",
    "Figure 7 compares the interband lags measured with EzTaoX to those from JAVELIN (left panel) and ICCF (right panel).",
    "We retrieve the ZTF light curves for these sources from the IPAC Infrared Science Archive (ZTF Team 2025) and truncate them to match the DR7 temporal baseline (i.e., MJD < 59400)."
  ]
}